WEBVTT

00:00.005 --> 00:01.306
<i>Previously, on "Suits":</i>

00:01.316 --> 00:02.950
- Tell Harvey how you feel.
- What?

00:02.985 --> 00:04.471
If you don't tell him
that soon,

00:04.473 --> 00:06.247
you might lose the chance
to tell him at all.

00:06.248 --> 00:09.409
I understand why you go after
the unattainable woman.

00:09.410 --> 00:11.777
You are titillated
by what you cannot have.

00:11.812 --> 00:13.278
But I can have her, Doc.

00:13.314 --> 00:15.447
Only if you choose
to be the bad boy.

00:15.483 --> 00:16.849
What if I want to be
the bad boy?

00:16.884 --> 00:18.750
I am happy to say,
my friend,

00:18.786 --> 00:21.320
we both know that is not you.

00:21.355 --> 00:22.766
Paula said she doesn't
think we'd survive

00:22.790 --> 00:24.656
if you and I
keep working together.

00:24.792 --> 00:26.992
I want to stay here in the
position that I fought to get

00:27.027 --> 00:29.494
and that I love
and that I know I deserve.

00:29.530 --> 00:31.630
- You let Donna go.
- She left her letter

00:31.665 --> 00:33.398
of resignation on my desk.

00:33.434 --> 00:35.434
- I'm sorry, Harvey.
- You didn't make me do it.

00:35.469 --> 00:38.470
I chose to, and now
I'm choosing to undo it.

00:38.505 --> 00:41.573
- Are you okay?
- Will you come back?

00:41.609 --> 00:43.809
- Yes.
- Then I'm okay.

00:43.844 --> 00:45.722
The Dean of Admissions
is coming to check on your work

00:45.746 --> 00:47.212
tomorrow night, Miss Sazs.

00:47.247 --> 00:49.147
You mean Dean Hans
Von Schlongenhammer?

00:49.183 --> 00:50.794
You're going to get a hammer

00:50.818 --> 00:53.352
from the schlongen.
- Louis, this is my fiancé,

00:53.387 --> 00:55.220
Zander.
- Hey.

00:56.323 --> 00:58.190
<i>- What'd you see in him?</i>
<i>- I know.</i>

01:04.918 --> 01:07.619
Louis, we've been here
for 35 minutes,

01:07.654 --> 01:09.821
and you've barely said a word.

01:09.857 --> 01:11.757
What's going on?

01:11.792 --> 01:14.393
All right, you want
to know the truth?

01:14.428 --> 01:16.695
Last time I saw you,
you said I'm not the bad boy.

01:17.865 --> 01:20.432
But I thought,
"You know, why not?

01:20.467 --> 01:22.868
Why can't Louis Litt be
the bad boy just this once?"

01:22.903 --> 01:25.570
I see, so you continued
your affair with Sheila.

01:25.606 --> 01:28.240
And it was great.
I mean, I had the girl.

01:28.275 --> 01:30.342
I had the confidence.

01:30.377 --> 01:31.943
But then when I went
to meet her...

01:33.614 --> 01:35.480
He was there.
- He?

01:35.516 --> 01:37.883
The shithead that's she's
marrying, Zander Fuck Face.

01:37.918 --> 01:39.785
And how did seeing him
make you feel?

01:39.820 --> 01:41.520
How the hell do you think
it made me feel?

01:41.555 --> 01:42.866
It made me feel like someone
was ripping my heart out,

01:42.890 --> 01:44.434
shredding it to pieces,
and lighting it on fire

01:44.458 --> 01:46.258
right in front of me.

01:46.293 --> 01:47.893
- Good.
- Good?

01:47.928 --> 01:49.327
Did you not hear
what I just said?

01:49.363 --> 01:50.807
You want me to say it
again in German?

01:50.831 --> 01:53.432
I heard you, Louis.

01:53.467 --> 01:54.766
I said good

01:54.802 --> 01:56.435
because you may have
fooled yourself

01:56.470 --> 01:58.770
into believing
there was some future

01:58.806 --> 02:00.405
between you and Sheila.

02:00.441 --> 02:02.274
But coming face-to-face
with this Zander

02:02.309 --> 02:04.443
means you can now
face the truth.

02:04.478 --> 02:05.577
What truth is that?

02:05.612 --> 02:07.312
That if you do not end this,

02:07.347 --> 02:09.281
that terrible feeling
you had last night

02:09.316 --> 02:12.117
will only continue to grow.

02:12.152 --> 02:13.652
I know.

02:15.622 --> 02:17.122
You're right.

02:20.227 --> 02:22.160
It's time to let her go.

02:27.877 --> 02:30.177
- Judge Ralls?
- You remember me.

02:30.212 --> 02:31.678
Of course.

02:31.714 --> 02:33.480
You treated me fairly
during my trial.

02:33.516 --> 02:35.482
I'll never forget that.
- Good.

02:35.518 --> 02:37.784
Because I'm not just here
by accident.

02:40.089 --> 02:41.700
You're being accused
of overturning a verdict

02:41.724 --> 02:43.457
for personal gain.

02:43.492 --> 02:45.859
And if I lose, it could
cost me my judgeship.

02:45.895 --> 02:47.694
Forgive me for asking,
but why exactly

02:47.730 --> 02:48.962
are you coming
to me with this?

02:48.998 --> 02:50.964
Because you're a hell
of a lawyer.

02:51.000 --> 02:52.633
And like you said,
I always treated you

02:52.668 --> 02:55.035
fairly during your trial.
- Bullshit.

02:55.070 --> 02:57.671
How many other firms
you go to before coming to me?

02:59.608 --> 03:01.508
- Seven.
- That's what I thought.

03:01.544 --> 03:03.388
So you're not coming to me
because I know you're fair.

03:03.412 --> 03:05.879
You picked me because
anyone who takes on this case

03:05.915 --> 03:07.748
is gonna have to drop
at least one client,

03:07.783 --> 03:09.261
and you thought
you could come down here

03:09.285 --> 03:11.885
and guilt me into doing that.

03:11.921 --> 03:13.820
No, thanks.

03:14.054 --> 03:15.920
And what if that's true?

03:15.956 --> 03:19.057
I can't ask my firm
to drop a client right now.

03:19.092 --> 03:20.692
I'm sorry.

03:20.727 --> 03:21.960
You're sorry?

03:21.995 --> 03:23.428
You stood in my courtroom,

03:23.463 --> 03:26.331
said you'd been given a gift
and you wasted it.

03:26.366 --> 03:27.699
I've served for 20 years.

03:27.734 --> 03:29.412
They're accusing me
of something I didn't do,

03:29.436 --> 03:30.635
and I lose this,

03:30.670 --> 03:33.471
I lose everything
I've ever worked for.

03:33.507 --> 03:36.741
So did you mean that shit
you said to the jury or not?

