05:39.001 --> 05:41.702
- Mike, it's not even 9:00 yet.
- I know.

05:41.883 --> 05:43.560
I was as surprised
to find you here as you were.

05:43.584 --> 05:45.318
Well, I meant
it's not even 9:00

05:45.353 --> 05:47.331
and you're already coming to me
with that look on your face.

05:47.355 --> 05:48.621
What look on my face?

05:48.656 --> 05:50.489
The look that says
you're about to ask

05:50.525 --> 05:51.802
for something
that I won't want to do.

05:53.094 --> 05:54.660
Judge Ralls came to see me.

05:54.696 --> 05:56.507
You mean the judge
that oversaw your fraud case?

05:56.531 --> 05:58.208
She's been accused
of overturning a verdict

05:58.232 --> 06:00.366
for a company
that she has an interest in.

06:00.401 --> 06:01.867
- No.
- Harvey, I don't think

06:01.903 --> 06:04.437
she did it.
- We're trying to sign Techron.

06:04.472 --> 06:06.517
They've got a case that could
end up in front of Ralls.

06:06.541 --> 06:08.441
The second we agree
to represent her,

06:08.476 --> 06:10.710
we can kiss them good-bye.
- Okay, look, I...

06:10.745 --> 06:12.356
I don't want this to be
another prison case.

06:12.380 --> 06:13.857
So if you don't want
to do it, we won't, but...

06:13.881 --> 06:15.781
we were just on the right side
with Teddy.

06:15.817 --> 06:17.695
I thought it'd be nice for us
to be on the right side again.

06:17.719 --> 06:19.318
What do you mean us?

06:19.354 --> 06:21.198
Even if I said yes, you don't
need me to fight this.

06:21.222 --> 06:24.323
I heard about what happened
with Paula.

06:24.359 --> 06:25.869
I just thought that if we did
this thing together,

06:25.893 --> 06:27.827
maybe we could have some fun.

06:29.397 --> 06:31.664
In that case, get your shit.

06:31.699 --> 06:34.567
Brief me on the way.

06:34.602 --> 06:36.302
On our way where?

06:36.337 --> 06:38.738
If you know "A Few Good Men"
as well as you say you do,

06:38.773 --> 06:40.840
you'll be able to guess.

06:46.004 --> 06:47.670
- Thanks.
- Excuse me.

06:47.705 --> 06:49.605
Aren't you Donna Paulsen?

06:49.641 --> 06:52.642
I am, and who might you be?

06:52.677 --> 06:54.110
David Fox.

06:54.145 --> 06:55.812
Fox Commercial Leasing.
- Oh.

06:55.847 --> 06:57.458
I know who you are, Mr. Fox.
You own the building.

06:57.482 --> 06:58.781
Please, call me David.

06:58.817 --> 07:00.394
You know this isn't
the only building I own.

07:00.418 --> 07:02.485
Hmm, exactly how many
do you own?

07:02.520 --> 07:03.953
34.

07:03.988 --> 07:05.788
Well, David, if you think
telling me

07:05.824 --> 07:08.024
that you own 34 properties
is going to impress me,

07:08.059 --> 07:09.725
you just might be right.

07:09.761 --> 07:11.539
Well, I do love being right,
and you know what?

07:11.563 --> 07:14.163
I wish I could keep doing this
all day, but unfortunately,

07:14.199 --> 07:16.933
this isn't a social call.

07:16.968 --> 07:19.168
You want us to quadruple
our security deposit?

07:19.204 --> 07:21.771
You took Jessica Pearson's
name off the wall,

07:21.806 --> 07:24.807
and then you declared you want
nothing to do with her.

07:24.843 --> 07:27.877
That is a material change
in your firm.

07:27.912 --> 07:29.846
It could affect
your ability to make rent.

07:30.357 --> 07:32.190
Look.

07:32.225 --> 07:34.259
We did distance ourselves
from Jessica Pearson.

07:34.294 --> 07:35.571
But we also restructured
the firm,

07:35.595 --> 07:37.128
and we're stronger than ever.

07:37.164 --> 07:38.408
And if you need me
to show you the books

07:38.432 --> 07:39.831
to prove it,
I'm happy to do that.

07:39.866 --> 07:41.144
That's not gonna be
necessary, Donna,

07:41.168 --> 07:42.478
but look, I've got
this board of directors

07:42.502 --> 07:45.036
that I have to contend with,
so if you could

07:45.072 --> 07:48.006
draft a letter documenting
exactly what you just told me

07:48.041 --> 07:52.110
and hand-deliver it
to my office,

07:52.145 --> 07:53.845
I just might able
to keep them at bay.

07:53.880 --> 07:55.258
You know, if you wanted me
to come to your office,

07:55.282 --> 07:56.981
you could have just asked.

07:57.017 --> 07:58.350
I thought I just did.

08:04.758 --> 08:05.802
Katrina,
drop what you're doing.

08:05.826 --> 08:07.158
I need my black swan.

08:07.194 --> 08:09.260
Let me guess.
Zander Epstein.

08:09.296 --> 08:10.962
What?
How could you know that?

08:10.997 --> 08:12.875
When I saw the announcement
about Sheila's wedding,

08:12.899 --> 08:14.366
I knew there'd eventually
be a duel.

08:14.401 --> 08:16.768
Which is why I already started
digging into him.

08:16.803 --> 08:17.880
Well, then tell me
what you got,

08:17.904 --> 08:19.982
because I need to beat
this clown 19 ways from Sunday,

08:20.006 --> 08:21.284
and I've never even
heard of him.

08:21.308 --> 08:23.208
The reason you haven't
heard of him is because

08:23.243 --> 08:26.544
he's an expert in a very small
subset of technology law.

08:26.580 --> 08:28.513
Well, shit. I don't know
anything about tech law.

08:28.548 --> 08:30.715
But what you do know about
is having a huge chip

08:30.751 --> 08:32.217
on your shoulder
and using it to beat

08:32.251 --> 08:34.352
the shit out of anyone
who stands in your way.

08:34.388 --> 08:36.321
That I do.

08:36.356 --> 08:38.056
This is gonna be
one hell of a duel.

08:38.091 --> 08:40.725
I know. He's gonna be
the Burr to your Hamilton.

08:41.928 --> 08:42.894
But Hamilton dies.

08:42.929 --> 08:44.829
Not this time, Louis.

08:44.865 --> 08:45.997
Not this time.

08:50.637 --> 08:53.104
I don't get it.
How could I have guessed this?

08:53.140 --> 08:55.407
They didn't go to batting cages
in "A Few Good Men."

08:55.442 --> 08:58.977
No, but Tom Cruise says he
can think better with his bat.

08:59.012 --> 09:01.913
There is no way I could have
guessed that.

09:01.948 --> 09:03.815
All right, give me
the Cliff Notes.

09:03.850 --> 09:06.818
Two months ago,
PolyCode versus K Systems.

09:06.853 --> 09:08.720
Jury ruled in favor
of PolyCode.

09:08.755 --> 09:12.023
Ralls overturned the case
on its merits.

09:12.058 --> 09:14.125
Let me guess.
Whoever's representing PolyCode

09:14.161 --> 09:16.828
found out that Ralls has a ton
of money in K Systems.

09:16.863 --> 09:18.663
Exactly.

09:18.698 --> 09:19.998
But I talked
to her finance guy,

09:20.033 --> 09:21.733
and he says it's in a trust,

09:21.768 --> 09:23.513
it's blind, and he's willing
to put it in writing.

09:23.537 --> 09:24.969
Who's repping PolyCode?

09:25.005 --> 09:26.704
Smith and Devane.

09:26.740 --> 09:28.573
Well, they're not idiots.

09:28.608 --> 09:30.720
They've got to figure that
we could find proof like that.

09:30.744 --> 09:32.510
Yeah, so the only
question is,

09:32.546 --> 09:33.623
why do they think
they have a shot?

09:37.818 --> 09:40.852
Wait a second, what if they
don't think they have a shot?

09:40.887 --> 09:42.420
What are you talking about?

09:42.456 --> 09:43.900
You said you didn't want
to represent Ralls

09:43.924 --> 09:47.192
because it could affect
another case we might try.

09:47.227 --> 09:48.726
She gets put in review,

09:48.762 --> 09:50.540
she's gonna be kicked off
the bench for six months.

09:50.564 --> 09:52.697
Holy shit, they want
her off so she won't

09:52.732 --> 09:54.866
find against a different client
in an upcoming case.

09:54.901 --> 09:56.768
Which means if we can
get her to recuse herself

09:56.803 --> 09:58.848
from whatever the case is--
- They'll drop this bullshit

09:58.872 --> 10:00.004
like a hot potato.

10:00.040 --> 10:01.673
Well, look at that.

10:01.708 --> 10:03.575
I am having fun.

10:03.610 --> 10:05.243
Now I'm having even more fun

10:05.278 --> 10:06.611
because you hit like a monkey

10:06.646 --> 10:08.279
trying to have sex
with a buffalo.

10:09.416 --> 10:11.483
What kind of nature films
did you watch as a kid?

10:11.518 --> 10:13.184
I didn't watch any.

10:13.220 --> 10:15.153
I was too busy learning
how to hit a baseball.

10:22.548 --> 10:24.448
Ugh, what are you doing here?

10:24.483 --> 10:25.950
You said you're
the better lawyer.

10:25.985 --> 10:27.384
I thought we'd
put it to the test.

10:27.420 --> 10:28.953
You really want
to pick a fight

10:28.988 --> 10:30.888
with me in tech law?
I wrote the book on it.

10:30.923 --> 10:32.367
I don't care what
you wrote the book on.

10:32.391 --> 10:33.535
I just took my glove off
and slapped you

10:33.559 --> 10:34.458
in the face with it,
so are you gonna

10:34.493 --> 10:36.427
run to Mommy
or pick up a pistol?

10:36.462 --> 10:38.006
You don't have the standing
to bring this suit.

10:38.030 --> 10:39.964
Yes, I do, because one
of the massive banks

10:39.999 --> 10:41.565
in the area
I wrote the book on

10:41.601 --> 10:44.335
has a 40% stake
in Office Warehouse.

10:44.370 --> 10:46.270
And the new microchips
in your printers

10:46.305 --> 10:47.805
lock out our ink cartridge.

10:47.840 --> 10:49.373
Oh, I get it.

10:49.408 --> 10:52.009
You don't like
that we have the most exquisite

10:52.044 --> 10:53.777
piece of equipment ever made

10:53.813 --> 10:56.213
and the only cartridge
that will ever get to fill it

10:56.249 --> 11:00.317
with the full range of
proprietary ink again is mine.

11:00.353 --> 11:01.863
How dare you talk
about Sheila like that?

11:01.887 --> 11:03.387
Sheila?

11:03.422 --> 11:05.334
I thought we were talking
about who's the better lawyer.

11:05.358 --> 11:07.057
Because let me assure you,
no matter where

11:07.093 --> 11:09.293
this little charade ends,
you're gonna be left standing

11:09.328 --> 11:12.963
alone with nothing but
your Dictaphone in your hand.

11:12.999 --> 11:14.209
She told you
about my Dictaphone?

11:14.233 --> 11:16.767
She told me everything.

11:16.802 --> 11:18.102
Now get out of my office.

11:18.137 --> 11:19.737
I have to call my fiancée
and tell her

11:19.772 --> 11:21.772
I have a nuisance suit
to take care of.

11:27.545 --> 11:28.945
All right.

11:28.980 --> 11:30.179
Let's make this quick.

11:30.215 --> 11:32.415
I only have a 15-minute recess.

11:32.450 --> 11:33.883
This won't take
that much time

11:33.918 --> 11:35.952
