Are you kidding me?

24:10.684 --> 24:12.517
She's stepping down
from a huge case

24:12.553 --> 24:14.431
that you have pending with her
which we all know

24:14.455 --> 24:15.887
is what this
is really about.

24:15.923 --> 24:18.223
What this is really about,
Mr. Ross,

24:18.258 --> 24:20.025
is removing a judge
from the bench

24:20.060 --> 24:22.194
who's demonstrated an inability
to follow the law.

24:22.229 --> 24:24.229
Bullshit. She followed
the law in your case.

24:24.264 --> 24:25.964
You just didn't like
the result.

24:25.999 --> 24:27.444
Then why don't you ask her
if she followed the law

24:27.468 --> 24:29.000
in the Sullivan case
12 years ago?

24:29.036 --> 24:30.213
What the hell
are you talking about?

24:30.237 --> 24:33.171
Your client takes matters
into her own hands.

24:33.207 --> 24:36.408
She did it 12 years ago.
She did it two months ago.

24:36.443 --> 24:38.477
God knows how many times
she's done it in between.

24:38.512 --> 24:40.579
But she's never going
to do it again.

24:40.614 --> 24:42.948
That woman has more integrity
in her little finger

24:42.983 --> 24:44.394
than you have in your entire--
- Mike, that's enough.

24:44.418 --> 24:45.984
You make an accusation
like that,

24:46.019 --> 24:47.486
you better
damn well have proof.

24:47.521 --> 24:49.488
Because if you smear
this woman's reputation

24:49.523 --> 24:53.258
without cause, I will make it
my life's mission to bury you.

24:53.293 --> 24:56.595
Then instead of coming
at me with empty threats,

24:56.630 --> 24:59.331
why don't you ask
your client what she did?

25:05.338 --> 25:07.705
What are you doing
bursting in here unannounced?

25:07.740 --> 25:09.773
We just came
from Smith and Devane.

25:09.809 --> 25:11.575
They're throwing around
some Sullivan case

25:11.611 --> 25:13.451
like it means something,
and you better tell us

25:13.479 --> 25:15.646
what they're talking about
right now, or we're gone.

25:18.217 --> 25:20.184
It was 12 years ago.

25:20.219 --> 25:22.319
I was a new judge.

25:22.355 --> 25:25.356
And there was a 16-year-old kid
with the worst public defender

25:25.391 --> 25:27.157
I've ever seen.

25:27.193 --> 25:30.294
It was bad enough I had
to rule in favor of this boy

25:30.329 --> 25:32.796
being tried as an adult,

25:32.832 --> 25:35.799
but when he was offered
a plea deal and this moron

25:35.835 --> 25:38.269
wanted to take it to trial,

25:38.304 --> 25:40.671
I couldn't sit by
and watch.

25:40.706 --> 25:43.407
I don't understand. Why not
just declare a mistrial?

25:43.442 --> 25:45.242
Because having
a shitty lawyer

25:45.278 --> 25:46.610
isn't grounds for that.

25:46.646 --> 25:48.279
So instead
you had direct contact

25:48.314 --> 25:49.992
with the defendant?
- Harvey, take it easy.

25:50.016 --> 25:51.448
She was just trying
to help a kid.

25:51.484 --> 25:53.328
I don't give a shit if
she's trying to cure cancer.

25:53.352 --> 25:55.486
It's illegal.
She didn't tell us about it.

25:55.521 --> 25:57.321
I'm not losing a client
for a judge

25:57.356 --> 26:00.090
who can't even tell
her own lawyers the truth.

26:00.126 --> 26:03.460
You want to know what kind
of judge I am?

26:03.496 --> 26:06.163
Anita Gibbs came to me
to wiretap your phones

26:06.198 --> 26:07.698
because she knew in her gut

26:07.733 --> 26:10.000
he was a fraud
and you were in on it.

26:10.036 --> 26:12.036
She had everyone
from the attorney general

26:12.071 --> 26:14.004
to the governor's office call
to make me do it,

26:14.040 --> 26:15.306
I said no

26:15.341 --> 26:17.308
because they didn't have
probable cause.

26:17.343 --> 26:19.076
Are you saying I owe you?

26:19.111 --> 26:21.512
I'm saying I made one mistake

26:21.547 --> 26:23.647
12 years ago,

26:23.683 --> 26:25.349
and our system relies

26:25.384 --> 26:29.386
on having people like me
up on that bench

26:29.422 --> 26:32.323
so that when people like you
get in front of us,

26:32.358 --> 26:34.959
you don't go straight
to prison.

26:42.399 --> 26:43.710
Katrina, if you're here
to tell me we've got nothing,

26:43.734 --> 26:45.200
it's gonna have to wait
because--

26:45.235 --> 26:46.701
I'm not here
to tell you that, Louis.

26:46.737 --> 26:48.670
I'm here to tell you
we have everything.

26:48.705 --> 26:50.171
- What?
- I heard him talk

26:50.207 --> 26:51.606
about digital versus analog,

26:51.641 --> 26:53.441
which got me thinking.

26:53.477 --> 26:56.311
Tech law has its basis
in copyright law,

26:56.346 --> 26:57.812
which means--
- Holy shit.

26:57.848 --> 26:59.280
Xerox applies after all.

26:59.316 --> 27:00.648
Exactly.

27:00.684 --> 27:02.417
We got him.

27:02.452 --> 27:03.830
All you have to do
is show him this,

27:03.854 --> 27:06.454
and he will collapse
like a premature soufflé.

27:08.792 --> 27:10.625
You do it.

27:10.660 --> 27:12.160
- Louis, I can't.
- Why not?

27:12.195 --> 27:13.639
Because the whole reason
we're doing this

27:13.663 --> 27:15.196
is to give you the satisfaction

27:15.232 --> 27:16.476
of seeing that bastard
humiliated.

27:16.500 --> 27:18.266
Katrina,
don't you understand?

27:18.301 --> 27:19.379
If that happens, he's gonna say
something horrible,

27:19.403 --> 27:21.403
then I'm gonna say something
horrible back,

27:21.438 --> 27:23.738
and then I'm gonna
be tempted to tell him that--

27:23.774 --> 27:26.608
Tell him what?

27:26.643 --> 27:28.376
Never mind.
I can handle it.

27:28.412 --> 27:30.045
Louis, what's going on?

27:30.080 --> 27:31.691
What's going on is,
I do not want to sully you

27:31.715 --> 27:33.181
with my sordid personal life.

27:33.216 --> 27:34.716
I got myself into this mess,

27:34.751 --> 27:37.519
and you did everything you can
to get me out of it.

27:37.554 --> 27:40.188
The rest I have to do myself,
so thank you.

27:55.305 --> 27:57.072
Donna, can I talk to you
for a second?

27:57.107 --> 27:59.507
No, Rachel, you can't because
I'm too busy freaking out.

27:59.543 --> 28:01.309
Freaking out about what?
We had him.

28:01.344 --> 28:02.644
It didn't work.

28:02.679 --> 28:04.123
There's a clause
in our lease that says

28:04.147 --> 28:05.458
if we skip arbitration,
he can kick us out

28:05.482 --> 28:06.381
in 30 days, not 90.

28:06.416 --> 28:08.383
No, that's only if we

28:08.418 --> 28:09.451
started the litigation.

28:09.486 --> 28:10.785
We didn't.
He sued us.

28:10.821 --> 28:13.254
- Not officially.
- What?

28:13.290 --> 28:15.123
You told me that--
- I didn't understand

28:15.158 --> 28:17.225
when I told you.

28:17.260 --> 28:18.404
Donna, you have
to tell Harvey.

28:18.428 --> 28:19.227
- I can't.
- Okay, then

28:19.262 --> 28:20.195
you have to tell Louis.

28:20.230 --> 28:23.064
Paula wanted Harvey
to get rid of me.

28:23.100 --> 28:24.666
What--

28:24.701 --> 28:26.434
what are you talking about?

28:26.470 --> 28:29.471
I didn't tell you
the whole story.

28:29.506 --> 28:31.517
She wanted me gone, and Harvey
didn't want to fire me,

28:31.541 --> 28:34.042
so he went to Stu Buzzini
and got him to offer me a job.

28:34.077 --> 28:35.721
And I was gonna to take it,
but then at the last minute,

28:35.745 --> 28:37.345
Harvey changed his mind.

28:39.416 --> 28:41.316
He chose me over her.

28:42.886 --> 28:45.353
And it was only a few days ago,
and I can't be responsible

28:45.388 --> 28:49.257
for losing the only home
that this firm has ever had.

28:49.292 --> 28:51.159
Donna, I understand
all of that.

28:51.194 --> 28:53.995
But if you let your guilt
keep you

28:54.030 --> 28:56.164
from giving him a chance
to fix this thing

28:56.199 --> 28:58.166
before it's too late,

28:58.201 --> 29:00.435
he's gonna wish
you took that job.

29:00.470 --> 29:02.070
Okay.

29:03.607 --> 29:05.006
I'll tell him.

29:06.276 --> 29:08.516
Harvey. I've gone through
the files on the Sullivan case.

29:08.891 --> 29:10.457
You did what?

29:10.492 --> 29:11.792
Why would you do that?

29:11.827 --> 29:13.627
Because the panel's
in two days.

29:13.662 --> 29:14.628
We need to be prepared
for whatever

29:14.663 --> 29:15.774
they're gonna throw at Ralls.

29:15.798 --> 29:17.731
No, we don't,
because I'm not risking

29:17.766 --> 29:18.910
having to drop another client

29:18.934 --> 29:20.400
for someone
who lied to my face.

29:20.436 --> 29:22.769
I'm sorry,
were you in that room?

29:22.805 --> 29:24.971
If she hadn't denied that
wiretap, I wouldn't have been

29:25.007 --> 29:26.907
the only one in prison,
and you know that.

29:26.942 --> 29:28.920
Okay, why do you think she
brought that up to you, Mike?

29:28.944 --> 29:30.755
I don't know. Maybe
to show us why she deserves

29:30.779 --> 29:32.612
to be on the bench.
- Bullshit.

29:32.648 --> 29:34.426
She did it to make you feel
like you owe her something,

29:34.450 --> 29:36.516
which is why she came to you
in the first place.

29:36.552 --> 29:37.784
It's because you're a sucker.

29:39.388 --> 29:41.388
Okay.
Well, you know what, Harvey?

29:41.423 --> 29:42.856
I'd rather be a sucker
than someone

29:42.891 --> 29:45.692
who refuses to sacrifice
anything for anyone else.

29:45.728 --> 29:47.360
What the fuck did you
just say to me?

29:47.396 --> 29:50.497
I said I don't give a shit
what we lose.

29:50.532 --> 29:52.466
This woman did us a favor,

29:52.501 --> 29:54.279
and I'm not gonna hang her
out to dry just because

29:54.303 --> 29:56.303
you don't want to sacrifice
a piece of business.

29:56.338 --> 29:58.772
I sacrificed more
than just business this week

29:58.807 --> 30:00.841
all because you couldn't keep
your mouth shut.

30:00.876 --> 30:02.642
Are you ser--
Are you really

30:02.678 --> 30:04.277
making this
about Donna right now

30:04.313 --> 30:05.690
when we got a woman's future
on the line?

30:05.714 --> 30:06.813
Don't give me that shit.

30:06.849 --> 30:08.348
You made it about Donna

30:08.383 --> 30:09.816
when you said
I couldn't sacrifice.

30:09.852 --> 30:11.918
I sacrificed everything.

30:11.954 --> 30:13.920
- Harvey--
- Enough.

30:13.956 --> 30:15.734
You said you didn't want this
to be another prison case.

30:15.758 --> 30:17.691
Well, it is
another prison case,

30:17.726 --> 30:21.895
and I'm saying
we're dropping it.

30:21.930 --> 30:24.097
Okay, well, as long as we're
talking about sacrifice

30:24.133 --> 30:27.234
and prison, one of us went
to prison for the other one,

30:27.269 --> 30:29.436
and the woman you're
about to cut loose?

30:29.471 --> 30:31.338
She's the reason
that was possible.

30:42.219 --> 30:43.252
Thanks.

30:48.192 --> 30:49.737
Did you come to drop
this thing in person?

30:49.761 --> 30:51.294
Because if you're nice,

30:51.329 --> 30:53.396
I might let you avoid
being humiliated in court.

30:53.431 --> 30:54.775
You're the one
who's gonna be humiliated

30:54.799 --> 30:56.065
if this goes to court.

30:56.100 --> 30:58.034
Oh, good playground retort,
Litt.

30:58.069 --> 31:00.247
Then again, I guess a loser
like you had a lot of practice.

31:00.271 --> 31:02.838
How's this for a retort,
Zander?

31:05.176 --> 31:07.710
We go to court, that's
what everyone's gonna see.

31:12.016 --> 31:13.816
- What do you want?
- $30 million.

31:13.985 --> 31:15.333
And I want it written
in the settlement

31:15.334 --> 31:17.069
that Louis Litt
is a superior lawyer

31:17.070 --> 31:18.039
to Zander Epstein.

31:18.040 --> 31:19.405
- No way.
- Yeah way.

31:19.441 --> 31:21.207
- You're really that petty?
- You can bury it

31:21.243 --> 31:23.843
in the fine print
if you want.

31:23.879 --> 31:25.511
You can put it in Latin
if you want.

31:25.547 --> 31:27.180
But it's going in there,

31:27.215 --> 31:29.983
and you're always gonna
know it's there.

31:30.018 --> 31:31.417
Okay.

31:31.453 --> 31:34.754
If that's what it takes
to make you whole,

31:34.789 --> 31:37.891
then we have a deal,
but one thing.

31:37.926 --> 31:40.927
When I get home tonight,
remember who's waiting for me.

31:40.962 --> 31:43.897
And she's gonna cook me dinner,
she's gonna rub my feet,

31:43.932 --> 31:45.398
she's gonna tell me
she loves me,

31:45.433 --> 31:48.134
and we are never gonna
think of you again.

31:48.169 --> 31:50.336
Well, maybe on
our 50th wedding anniversary,

31:50.372 --> 31:54.007
we'll laugh about the guy
she almost ended up with,

31:54.042 --> 31:55.942
if we can even remember
your name.

31:58.947 --> 32:01.114
Now it's $50 million.

32:01.149 --> 32:03.850
And that's take it or leave it.

32:16.056 --> 32:17.322
Look, whatever it is,

32:17.357 --> 32:18.957
I'm kind of in the middle
of something.

32:18.992 --> 32:20.436
Well, I hope you're
in the middle of keeping

32:20.460 --> 32:22.394
Ralls on the bench.
- Maybe.

32:23.864 --> 32:26.197
Mike, I'm sorry
about last night.

32:26.233 --> 32:28.099
Truth is, it's been
an emotional week,

32:28.135 --> 32:30.735
and when you accused me
of never sacrificing--

32:30.771 --> 32:31.851
I shouldn't have said that.

32:33.240 --> 32:36.308
You've sacrificed for me
hundreds of times.

32:36.343 --> 32:38.343
I know that.
- More like thousands.

32:40.747 --> 32:42.647
Now, what do you got?

32:42.683 --> 32:45.183
Well, I got to thinking,

32:45.218 --> 32:47.152
how the hell did
that woman even know

32:47.187 --> 32:48.653
about what Ralls
did with Sullivan?

32:48.689 --> 32:50.655
I'm guessing
you've got an answer.

32:50.691 --> 32:53.258
Turns out that shitty
public defender--

32:53.293 --> 32:55.727
Smith and Devane hired him
six months ago.

32:55.762 --> 32:58.029
But the thing is,
six months ago,

32:58.065 --> 32:59.976
her docket hadn't been set
that far in the future.

33:00.000 --> 33:02.067
Which means this whole thing
was a setup

33:02.102 --> 33:03.802
for a case
that already happened.

33:03.837 --> 33:06.204
Think about it.
She gets thrown off the bench,

33:06.224 --> 33:08.258
every one of her rulings
for the last seven years

33:08.293 --> 33:10.026
is automatically subject
to appeal.

33:10.061 --> 33:12.061
Mike, this is great.
We got 'em.

33:12.097 --> 33:15.732
The only problem is,
I can't figure out which case

33:15.767 --> 33:16.978
because Smith and Devane didn't

33:17.002 --> 33:19.105
represent anyone
she ruled against.

33:19.106 --> 33:21.373
Well, what kind of cases did
she hear during that period?

33:21.408 --> 33:23.241
Mostly federal antitrust.

33:24.578 --> 33:26.812
Then I know who can help us.

33:33.921 --> 33:35.620
Sheila.

33:35.656 --> 33:37.122
What are you doing here?

33:37.310 --> 33:39.043
I talked to Zander earlier,
and he told me

33:39.079 --> 33:40.478
you two had
a settlement meeting.

33:40.513 --> 33:42.480
Is that what he said?

33:42.515 --> 33:45.149
I would describe it as more
of a beatdown, but whatever.

33:46.519 --> 33:48.853
- Thank you, Louis.
- Why are you thanking me?

33:50.090 --> 33:52.657
- For not telling him about us.
- Never crossed my mind.

33:52.692 --> 33:54.325
You asked me not to,
so I didn't.

33:54.361 --> 33:56.928
And now I have to ask you
for one more thing.

33:58.665 --> 34:00.365
Please let this case go.

34:00.400 --> 34:02.934
- What?
- Give him a way to save face,

34:02.969 --> 34:04.702
and let this thing go.

34:04.738 --> 34:06.315
I gave him a way.
It's called a settlement.

34:06.339 --> 34:08.072
No, you jacked up
the settlement

34:08.108 --> 34:09.706
and added in some nonsense

34:09.743 --> 34:11.152
about admitting
you're the better man.

34:11.177 --> 34:13.011
I am the better man.

34:13.045 --> 34:15.713
Then prove it
by being the bigger man.

34:15.748 --> 34:17.014
- Sheila--
- Louis,

34:17.050 --> 34:18.983
I'm getting married
in a few days,

34:19.018 --> 34:21.985
and all my fiancé
can think about is you.

34:22.022 --> 34:24.188
You won.

34:24.224 --> 34:27.425
You beat him,
and he knows it.

34:27.460 --> 34:29.827
Please do this for me.

34:29.862 --> 34:31.795
Because if you don't,

34:31.831 --> 34:33.576
you might as well
have just told him about us

34:33.600 --> 34:34.966
in the first place.

34:47.378 --> 34:48.978
Rachel, we need to talk.

34:49.013 --> 34:51.581
- What did Harvey say?
- I didn't go to Harvey.

34:51.616 --> 34:53.181
Donna, why not?

34:53.217 --> 34:55.284
Because he was busy
with something else,

34:55.320 --> 34:57.253
and I remembered
one of the reasons

34:57.288 --> 34:59.188
he promoted me
in the first place.

34:59.223 --> 35:00.756
I don't understand.

35:00.792 --> 35:02.525
Rachel, I know people.

35:02.560 --> 35:04.405
I know what makes them tick,
and I need you to pull

35:04.429 --> 35:06.362
another all-nighter
and help me make that asshole

35:06.397 --> 35:07.997
back the hell off.

35:09.167 --> 35:10.399
Okay.

35:14.038 --> 35:15.738
Louis, is this a bad time?

35:15.773 --> 35:17.239
What?

35:17.275 --> 35:19.028
No. What's going on?

35:19.288 --> 35:21.354
Smith and Devane's
trying to get rid of a judge

35:21.390 --> 35:23.657
to overturn a past ruling.

35:23.692 --> 35:26.059
Mike and I are trying to figure
out which case is big enough

35:26.244 --> 35:28.611
to be worth the risk.

35:28.647 --> 35:30.513
Glazer Bank v. Risa Ventures.

35:30.549 --> 35:32.126
You didn't even look
at the rest of the list.

35:32.150 --> 35:33.316
Oh, I didn't need to.

35:33.351 --> 35:35.485
Smith and Devane represent
Pomaville Industries.

35:35.520 --> 35:37.465
They've been wanting to merge
with Condor for two years.

35:37.489 --> 35:39.400
You overturn that precedent--
- Every dickhead on Wall Street

35:39.424 --> 35:41.324
would be swinging
from the chandeliers.

35:41.359 --> 35:42.492
Clear as day.

35:43.595 --> 35:45.995
You really are a maestro
with this stuff, aren't you?

35:46.031 --> 35:47.297
Thanks, Harvey.

35:48.467 --> 35:49.933
Night, Louis.

35:52.003 --> 35:53.436
Harvey, wait.

35:53.472 --> 35:55.638
I, uh...

35:55.674 --> 35:58.475
I could really use your advice
on something personal.

35:58.510 --> 36:02.445
But I know how you feel
about infidelity, and...

36:02.481 --> 36:04.280
Louis, my feelings
about that

36:04.316 --> 36:05.915
have to do with me
and me alone.

36:05.951 --> 36:07.762
I'm not gonna judge you
for making a different choice

36:07.786 --> 36:09.285
than I would.
- I appreciate that.

36:12.190 --> 36:14.524
Because I had an affair
with Sheila.

36:14.559 --> 36:16.793
Somehow things
got out of control,

36:16.828 --> 36:19.829
and found myself in a fight
with her fiancé.

36:19.865 --> 36:21.831
I went after his client,

36:21.867 --> 36:23.833
and I was about
to put him away.

36:25.837 --> 36:28.071
And now Sheila
wants me to tank it.

36:28.106 --> 36:30.907
Well, if you're asking
as managing partner,

36:30.942 --> 36:32.642
I'd say you better
not tank a case

36:32.677 --> 36:34.144
for a woman
you're sleeping with.

36:34.179 --> 36:36.279
I'm not asking you
as managing partner, Harvey.

36:38.116 --> 36:40.683
I'm asking you as my friend.

36:40.719 --> 36:44.487
Then, my friend,

36:44.523 --> 36:47.724
I say sometimes we have
to sacrifice our business

36:47.759 --> 36:49.559
for the people we care about.

36:54.099 --> 36:55.832
Thanks for this.

37:04.096 --> 37:06.831
Let me guess. You got here
early to inform the panel

37:06.866 --> 37:08.444
you're removing yourselves
from the case.

37:08.468 --> 37:11.268
No, we got here early
to inform you that you are.

37:11.304 --> 37:12.937
And once again,
why would I do that?

37:12.972 --> 37:14.872
Because you hired
a shitty defense attorney

37:14.907 --> 37:17.741
for the sole purpose of getting
dirt on an outstanding judge.

37:17.777 --> 37:19.643
Hiring a shitty lawyer
isn't against the law.

37:19.679 --> 37:22.880
No, but doing it so you can
set up a merger factory is.

37:22.915 --> 37:25.583
That's a great theory,
but you have no proof.

37:25.618 --> 37:27.151
Yes, we do.
Right here.

37:27.186 --> 37:29.653
You signed all six of these
companies within the last year.

37:29.689 --> 37:31.088
And we've got
signed affidavits

37:31.124 --> 37:32.857
from each one of them
saying that you

37:32.892 --> 37:35.593
approached them with an offer
to get their mergers through

37:35.628 --> 37:37.161
if they signed with you
in advance.

37:37.196 --> 37:38.896
Wasn't hard once
they realized

37:38.931 --> 37:40.965
this could rise to the level
of a criminal offense.

37:41.000 --> 37:43.267
And conspiracy
to alter judicial rulings

37:43.302 --> 37:45.936
is most definitely
a criminal offense.

37:45.972 --> 37:49.807
Which means if you don't drop
this thing right now,

37:49.842 --> 37:51.108
you'll end up in prison.

37:51.144 --> 37:52.610
It's up to you.

37:52.645 --> 37:54.089
They're gonna be here
in five minutes.

38:01.693 --> 38:04.093
Louis, what the hell is this?

38:04.129 --> 38:05.328
What does it look like?

38:05.363 --> 38:07.597
It looks like you let
this guy off the hook

38:07.632 --> 38:09.810
when you had him by the throat.
- It's a fair deal, Katrina.

38:09.834 --> 38:11.634
Our client's gonna be thrilled

38:11.670 --> 38:13.014
that they get paid
for an issue that they never

38:13.038 --> 38:14.504
even knew existed
in the first place.

38:14.539 --> 38:16.072
We didn't take this on
for the client.

38:16.107 --> 38:18.508
We did this for you.
- Well, then do this for me.

38:18.543 --> 38:20.510
- Louis.
- God damn it, just do it!

38:22.213 --> 38:25.014
Oh.

38:25.050 --> 38:27.517
She asked you to do this,
didn't she?

38:27.552 --> 38:29.485
I can't say no to her,
Katrina.

38:31.623 --> 38:32.822
I just can't.

38:32.857 --> 38:34.691
You're a good man,
Louis Litt.

38:36.928 --> 38:40.530
And someday you will find
someone who appreciates that.

38:57.445 --> 38:58.956
I see you've brought along
a friend this time.

38:58.980 --> 39:00.479
Oh, she's not just my friend.

39:00.515 --> 39:02.214
She's my lawyer.
- Mm, let me guess.

39:02.250 --> 39:03.894
You brought her along
to withdraw your suit

39:03.918 --> 39:04.928
'cause you finally
figured out there's no way

39:04.952 --> 39:06.418
to outsmart a man like me.

39:06.454 --> 39:08.053
No, she finally figured out

39:08.089 --> 39:09.455
what makes a man like you tick.

39:09.490 --> 39:11.323
And what makes you tick
is being able to say

39:11.359 --> 39:13.337
to every woman you meet
that you own the best buildings

39:13.361 --> 39:15.361
in the cities
with the best views.

39:15.396 --> 39:17.229
Mm, because if you
can't say that, then...

39:17.265 --> 39:19.231
people might notice
that you're really just

39:19.267 --> 39:21.066
an insecure little man
who builds buildings

39:21.102 --> 39:23.335
to cover up his weaknesses.

39:24.906 --> 39:26.105
Get out of my office.

39:26.140 --> 39:27.973
Oh, we will, but if we do,

39:28.009 --> 39:29.787
those views that you covet,
they're going away.

39:29.811 --> 39:31.622
- What are you talking about?
- Oh, did you think

39:31.646 --> 39:33.357
I just came here to tell you
I know what makes you tick?

39:33.381 --> 39:35.114
We now control
the air rights

39:35.149 --> 39:37.950
across from six of your
most prominent properties.

39:37.985 --> 39:41.253
So instead of their
unobstructed views of the park,

39:41.289 --> 39:43.722
your top-floor tenants
will now be looking out

39:43.758 --> 39:46.692
at a 40-foot-high
box of tampons.

39:46.727 --> 39:48.060
What do you want?

39:48.095 --> 39:49.929
I think you know
what we want.

39:49.964 --> 39:52.498
- You keep your lease as is.
- Not quite.

39:52.533 --> 39:53.710
We're gonna need you
to reimburse

39:53.734 --> 39:54.745
the cost of the air rights.

39:54.769 --> 39:57.036
And we'll take a 10% haircut
on our lease.

39:57.071 --> 39:58.582
I'd call you a name
right now, but I'm guessing

39:58.606 --> 39:59.817
you'd sue me.
- David, I really don't care

39:59.841 --> 40:00.940
what you call me right now

40:00.975 --> 40:02.975
because, like you said,
this isn't personal.

40:03.010 --> 40:04.109
It's just business.

40:06.442 --> 40:08.109
Here's our amended lease.

40:20.556 --> 40:22.490
Hey, how's it going?

40:22.525 --> 40:26.193
I just stopped by to tell you
that Judge Ralls called.

40:26.229 --> 40:28.296
She wanted to thank me.
- That's great.

40:28.331 --> 40:31.499
Only problem with that is,
she called me five minutes ago

40:31.534 --> 40:34.302
and told me
the exact same thing.

40:35.938 --> 40:38.472
Want to tell me
what you're really doing here?

40:38.508 --> 40:41.075
Why'd you say
that stuff to Donna?

40:41.110 --> 40:42.810
Because I care about her.

40:44.480 --> 40:46.400
I didn't want her to go
through life not knowing.

40:48.117 --> 40:50.284
- What about me?
- What about you?

40:50.320 --> 40:52.486
Did you think what it would
do to my relationship?

40:52.522 --> 40:54.088
I guess I thought
that if you were

40:54.123 --> 40:55.734
that solid with Paula,
it wouldn't matter.

40:55.758 --> 40:57.191
What if I went
to Logan Sanders

40:57.226 --> 40:58.706
and told him to go for it
with Rachel?

41:00.396 --> 41:02.430
Here's the difference.

41:02.465 --> 41:04.410
I would hope that you wouldn't
be rooting for Rachel

41:04.434 --> 41:08.369
to be with him, and you can
get mad at me or not, but...

41:08.404 --> 41:10.171
yeah, I guess maybe
I was rooting

41:10.206 --> 41:11.872
for Donna to be with you.

41:13.843 --> 41:15.309
Fair enough.

41:15.345 --> 41:16.811
I guess the truth is,
right now,

41:16.846 --> 41:18.779
I'm not looking to be
with anyone.

41:27.123 --> 41:28.589
Donna, are you busy?

41:28.624 --> 41:29.802
I was actually
just getting ready

41:29.826 --> 41:30.958
to go home for the night.

41:32.195 --> 41:34.228
I was just wondering
if there's a reason

41:34.263 --> 41:35.896
why I just got a new lease
on my desk

41:35.932 --> 41:37.932
that's 10% less
than our last one.

41:39.102 --> 41:41.736
I just wanted to thank you
for keeping me.

41:43.639 --> 41:45.740
What?
- If I knew it'd make you

41:45.775 --> 41:47.041
do stuff like that,

41:47.076 --> 41:48.843
I'd consider firing you
more often.

41:48.878 --> 41:51.345
Well, then let's just
consider this a one-time thing.

41:55.284 --> 41:57.718
Before you go...

41:57.754 --> 41:59.487
want me to pour us a drink?

41:59.522 --> 42:01.288
What do you say
we shake things up

42:01.324 --> 42:03.257
and make it two?

42:29.565 --> 42:31.565
Sheila, what are you
doing here?

42:31.601 --> 42:33.301
I left Zander.

42:35.438 --> 42:36.671
What?

42:36.706 --> 42:38.839
I realized he's not
the one for me.

42:39.776 --> 42:41.976
- But I thought you loved him.
- I don't.

42:42.011 --> 42:44.845
I love you.

42:44.881 --> 42:47.248
And I may have forgotten it
for a while.

42:47.283 --> 42:51.319
But in these last two weeks,
you've--you've excited me,

42:51.354 --> 42:53.554
you've gone to battle for me,

42:53.589 --> 42:55.890
and then you sacrificed for me.

42:55.925 --> 42:57.658
But what about children?

42:58.661 --> 43:00.294
You think I can't live
without children--

43:00.330 --> 43:02.697
No, I didn't,
but then I thought,

43:02.732 --> 43:04.298
fate brought us together,
Louis.

43:04.334 --> 43:06.133
Why don't we let fate decide

43:06.169 --> 43:08.602
whether or not
we have children?

43:08.638 --> 43:10.604
- I don't understand.
- Louis,

43:10.640 --> 43:13.307
I threw away my diaphragm.

43:17.413 --> 43:18.579
You're pulling the goalie?

43:18.614 --> 43:20.781
Yes, Louis.
I am.

43:22.819 --> 43:24.752
And I don't want
to role-play tonight.

43:24.787 --> 43:30.291
I just want to be Sheila Sazs
and Louis Litt.

43:34.163 --> 43:35.596
Well, come on.

43:38.334 --> 43:39.667
Let's go inside.

